In this subsection, "suitable work" means work:
that is within the capabilities of an individual;
for which the gross average weekly compensation exceeds the sum of the individual's weekly extended benefit amount plus any supplemental unemployment compensation benefits as defined in § 501(c)(17)(d) of the Internal Revenue Code that are payable to the individual for the week;
for which wages equal or exceed the higher of:
the minimum wage under § 6(a)(1) of the federal Fair Labor Standards Act, without regard to exemptions; or
an applicable State or local minimum wage;
that is listed with the Division of Workforce Development or offered in writing to the individual; and
that is suitable under § 8-1005 of this title to the extent that § 8-1005 of this title is not inconsistent with items (1) through (4) of this subsection.

To be eligible for extended benefits for a week during an eligibility period, an individual:
shall be unemployed for the week for which benefits are claimed;
shall meet each requirement of this title for regular benefits that applies to a claim for extended benefits;
shall not be subject to disqualification from receiving regular benefits;
may not have a right to unemployment allowances or benefits under the Railroad Unemployment Insurance Act or any other federal law that the United States Secretary of Labor specifies by regulation;
shall not have received and shall not be seeking unemployment benefits under the unemployment insurance law of Canada or if benefits have been sought under that law, shall have been finally determined by the appropriate unit not to be eligible; and
shall have exhausted regular benefits as provided in this subsection.
